SIMPLE: locker
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Locker
<hw>Lock"er</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>One who,
or that which, locks.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A drawer, cupboard, compartment, or chest, esp. one
in a ship, that may be closed with a lock.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Chain locker</b></col> <fld>(Naut.)</fld>, <cd>a
compartment in the hold of a vessel, for holding the chain cables.</cd>
-- <mcol><col><b>Davy Jones's locker</b></col>, <it>or</it>
<col><b>Davy's locker</b></col></mcol>. <cd>See <er>Davy
Jones</er>.</cd> -- <col><b>Shot locker</b></col>, <cd>a compartment
where shot are deposited.</cd> <rj><au>Totten.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Locket</ent>⟦br⟧
